The board shall issue a certificate as a certified interior designer and a certificate number to any person who:
Files an application with the board on a form prescribed by the board;
Submits written proof that the person has successfully passed the NCIDQ examination and therefore has met the education and internship requirements established by NCIDQ;
Meets the standards of education, experience, and testing established by the board under KRS 323.406(1); and
Submits the required certification fee to the board.
